definitions.definition: Located at or near the front.
examples: The front runner was thirty meters ahead of her nearest competitor.

definitions.definition: Pronounced with the highest part of the body of the tongue toward the front of the mouth , near the hard palate (most often describing a vowel ).
examples: The English word dress has a front vowel in most dialects.

definitions.definition: Closest or nearest , of a set of futures contracts which expire at particular times, or of the times they expire; ( typically, the front month or front year is the next calendar month or year after the current one ) .
